South Korea confirmed Wednesday that North Korean leader Kim Jong-Un&#8217;s half brother has been murdered in Malaysia, confirming reports of his assassination at Kuala Lumpur&#8217;s airport.&#8220;Our government is certain that the murdered man is Kim Jong-Nam,&#8221; said Chung Joon-Hee, a spokesman for Seoul&#8217;s unification ministry that handles inter-Korea affairs.-AFP